## Incident Summary
Repeated failed authentication attempts were detected from an external IP address, targeting multiple user accounts within a short time window.

## Detection Method
SIEM log analysis using Splunk search queries and statistical correlation.

## Timeline
- 08:03 â€“ Initial failed login attempt detected
- 08:05 â€“ Threshold exceeded indicating brute-force behavior

## Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
- Source IP: 203.0.113.45
- Targeted Accounts: admin, guest, root

## Impact Assessment
No confirmed account compromise detected. One successful login occurred after multiple failures, indicating potential credential exposure risk.

## Recommended Mitigations
- Block malicious IP addresses
- Enforce account lockout policies
- Implement Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
- Increase monitoring for authentication anomalies
